title: Stripe Minted More Than $2 Billion in Cash Last Year. Why Go Public?
body: Stripe is putting up the kind of numbers that would send its stock soaring, if it had public stock. The payments processing firm doubled its free cash flow last year to about $2.2 billion and grew revenues about 28% to $5.
